spec: multiprocessing_extra54
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html — Python multiprocessing module documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html#multiprocessing.Process — Process documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html#multiprocessing.pool.Pool — Pool documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/pool.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/process.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/context.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends multiprocessing_extra53.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs covered: Process/Queue/Pool/Lock/Event/Semaphore/Value/Array __name__/__module__, Process.__bases__[0].__name__=='BaseProcess', ProcessError/AuthenticationError/BufferTooShort/TimeoutError identity and bases, cpu_count/get_start_method/set_start_method/get_context/active_children __qualname__, exception __module__ and __len__(), context-bound class __qualname__.__len__() tables, Process method __qualname__.__len__() tables, Pool method tables, Process/Pool __mro__.__len__() tables, __all__ metadata, class __dict__.__class__.__name__/__qualname__ tables (extra52), Process/__class__.__name__=='type', cpu_count/__class__.__name__=='method', current_process/__class__.__name__=='function', ProcessError/AuthenticationError/__class__.__name__=='type' (extra45), Process/__class__.__module__=='builtins', current_process/__class__.__module__=='builtins', cpu_count/__class__.__module__=='builtins' (extra46), Pool/__doc__/__class__/__module__=='builtins' (extra50), Pool/__class__.__name__=='type' (multiprocessing_extra), Pool/active_children/ProcessError/AuthenticationError __class__.__module__.__eq__('builtins') (extra53), Process/__init__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function') (extra53)."
    - "This spec covers: multiprocessing.Process __repr__.__class__.__name__ — no prior multiprocessing spec has captured any __repr__.__class__ attribute. Process defines __repr__ in Lib/multiprocessing/process.py (BaseProcess.__repr__) as a plain Python function, so Process.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Also: multiprocessing.Pool.__repr__.__class__.__name__ — mp.Pool is a bound method object (not a class); a bound method's __repr__ is a method-wrapper, so Pool.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper'. Also: multiprocessing.pool.Pool.__repr__.__class__.__name__ — the actual Pool class from multiprocessing.pool defines __repr__ as a Python function; __repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Also: Process.__weakref__.__class__.__name__ == 'getset_descriptor'. Also: ProcessError/AuthenticationError __repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' (inherit from BaseException C slot)."
    - "multiprocessing.Process.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Process inherits from BaseProcess which defines __repr__ in Lib/multiprocessing/process.py as a plain Python function. Plain Python functions are objects of the built-in 'function' type, so Process.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. No prior multiprocessing spec has captured any __repr__.__class__ attribute. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.Pool.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper'. In the multiprocessing module-level namespace, Pool is a bound method of the DefaultContext singleton (not the Pool class from multiprocessing.pool). A bound method object's __repr__ is a C-level method-wrapper (the 'method' type's __repr__ slot bound to the method instance). Therefore Pool.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.Process.__weakref__.__class__.__name__ == 'getset_descriptor'. Process is a pure-Python class defined in Lib/multiprocessing/process.py; Python automatically provides a __weakref__ getset_descriptor for weakref support. No prior multiprocessing spec captured __weakref__.__class__.__name__. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.ProcessError.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. ProcessError is a subclass of Exception → BaseException (C type). BaseException defines __repr__ as a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor). ProcessError does not override __repr__ in Python, so it inherits the C-level wrapper_descriptor. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.AuthenticationError.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. AuthenticationError is a subclass of ProcessError → Exception → BaseException (C type); it inherits BaseException.__repr__ which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor). Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "Note: multiprocessing.Pool is a bound method of DefaultContext in the multiprocessing module-level namespace, NOT the Pool class from multiprocessing.pool. The Pool class (multiprocessing.pool.Pool) defines __repr__ as a Python function so pool.Pool.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. But mp.Pool.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper' because mp.Pool is a method instance, not a class. This spec uses the module-level mp.Pool (method-wrapper) for consistency with prior specs. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# multiprocessing Process/Pool __repr__.__class__.__name__ — extra54
#
# Process defines __repr__ via BaseProcess in Lib/multiprocessing/process.py
# as a plain Python function:
#   Process.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'
#
# mp.Pool is a bound method (DefaultContext.Pool bound method), so its __repr__
# is a C-level method-wrapper (bound slot from the 'method' type):
#   Pool.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper'
#
# No prior multiprocessing spec has captured any __repr__.__class__ attribute.
# Extra54 introduces this dimension in the mprepr54 namespace.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table multiprocessing_extra54.process_pool_repr_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing Process/Pool __repr__.__class__.__name__ in mprepr54 namespace — Process defines __repr__ as Python function ('function'); mp.Pool is a bound method whose __repr__ is a method-wrapper; no prior mp spec captured any __repr__.__class__ attribute"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: mprepr54reprname

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [Process, Process.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["function"],       true, "Process.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'function' — Process inherits BaseProcess.__repr__ defined in Lib/multiprocessing/process.py as a plain Python function; first __repr__.__class__.__name__ check in any multiprocessing spec"]
    - [Pool,    Pool.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,    ["method-wrapper"], true, "Pool.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper' — mp.Pool is a bound method of DefaultContext (not the Pool class); a bound method's __repr__ is a C-level method-wrapper bound to the method instance"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# multiprocessing Process __weakref__.__class__.__name__ — extra54
#
# Process is a pure-Python class defined in Lib/multiprocessing/process.py.
# Python automatically provides a __weakref__ getset_descriptor for pure-Python
# classes. Therefore:
#   Process.__weakref__.__class__.__name__ == 'getset_descriptor'
#
# No prior multiprocessing spec has captured __weakref__.__class__.__name__.
# Extra54 introduces this dimension in the mprepr54 namespace.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant multiprocessing_extra54.Process_weakref_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Process.__weakref__.__class__.__name__ == 'getset_descriptor' — Process is a pure-Python class defined in Lib/multiprocessing/process.py; Python automatically provides a __weakref__ getset_descriptor slot; first __weakref__.__class__.__name__ check in any multiprocessing spec"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Process.__weakref__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["getset_descriptor"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# multiprocessing exception __repr__.__class__.__name__ — extra54
#
# ProcessError and AuthenticationError are subclasses of Exception → BaseException.
# BaseException is implemented in C and defines __repr__ as a C-level slot
# wrapper (wrapper_descriptor). Neither ProcessError nor AuthenticationError
# override __repr__ in Python, so they both inherit the C-level slot:
#   ProcessError.__repr__.__class__.__name__        == 'wrapper_descriptor'
#   AuthenticationError.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'
#
# No prior multiprocessing spec has captured exception __repr__.__class__.__name__.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table multiprocessing_extra54.exception_repr_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing exception __repr__.__class__.__name__ in mprepr54 namespace — ProcessError/AuthenticationError inherit BaseException.__repr__ C-level slot wrapper ('wrapper_descriptor'); no prior mp spec captured exception __repr__.__class__.__name__"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: mprepr54excrepr

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [ProcessError,        ProcessError.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,        ["wrapper_descriptor"], true, "ProcessError.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — ProcessError subclasses Exception → BaseException (C type); inherits BaseException.__repr__ C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor); first exception __repr__.__class__.__name__ check in any multiprocessing spec"]
    - [AuthenticationError, AuthenticationError.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["wrapper_descriptor"], true, "AuthenticationError.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — AuthenticationError subclasses ProcessError → Exception → BaseException (C type); inherits BaseException.__repr__ C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Standalone invariants — extra54
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant multiprocessing_extra54.Process_repr_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Process.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'function' — Process inherits BaseProcess.__repr__ defined in Lib/multiprocessing/process.py as a plain Python function; the 'function' type is the built-in function type; first __repr__.__class__.__name__ check in any multiprocessing spec"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Process.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["function"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra54.Pool_repr_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Pool.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper' — mp.Pool is a bound method of DefaultContext (not the Pool class from multiprocessing.pool); a bound method object's __repr__ is a C-level method-wrapper; contrasts with Process which has 'function' __repr__"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Pool.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["method-wrapper"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra54.ProcessError_repr_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.ProcessError.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — ProcessError inherits BaseException.__repr__ which is a C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor); exception classes from C expose __repr__ as wrapper_descriptor"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: ProcessError.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["wrapper_descriptor"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra54.AuthenticationError_repr_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.AuthenticationError.__repr__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor' — AuthenticationError subclasses ProcessError → Exception → BaseException (C type); inherits BaseException.__repr__ C-level slot wrapper (wrapper_descriptor)"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: AuthenticationError.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["wrapper_descriptor"]
  expected: true
